Job Summary

An independent contributor role responsible for developing the channels and alliances and many others to meet the channel alliance relationships in the assigned region. The successful candidate will have broad knowledge and demonstrated success in developing and securing successful reseller partnerships. This role will be responsible to develop and build long term strategic relationships with possible channel and alliance partners through the development and deployment of clear and actionable channel and alliance strategies within the assigned region for the Cyber Security distribution business.

Duties & Responsibilities

Business unit “Cyber Security”
• Drive channel and alliance product and platform related revenue for assigned region;
• Responsible for delivering on quarterly and annual sales revenue based on the Alliance resale of product and platform offerings;
• Identify new channel partners and develop/manage existing partners in the assigned region;
• Achieve... targets as agreed with respective channel partners. Manage day-to-day business relationship with channel partners;
• Identify and create new business opportunities with channel partners focused on revenue and strategic market impact;
• Communicate consistently with channel partners and internal stakeholders, manage issues, resolve conflicts and enable support;
• Help channel partners build (pre)Sales / Sales and Post Sales capacity and capability on product and platform offerings;
• Create, implement and manage channel partner onboarding and training program. Drive training and certification in partner ecosystem;
• Support strategy and pipeline with Senior Management and confirm channel partner capabilities prior to deal is signed;
• Participate in tender/RFQ/RFP/RFI;

Job Holder’s Specifications
• Diploma and above in IT, Business IT, Business Administration, or a related field, or equivalent work experience.
• 5+ years of sales experiences in the IT industry; experiences in sales of Cybersecurity products and platforms would be highly advantages;
• Experience in business development planning and execution to drive sales pipeline, demand-gen, and enablement with channel partners;
• Passion for working with partners. Ability to understand channel partner ecosystem, business drivers and ability to establish buy-in at all levels;
• Market knowledge and understanding (IT industry, Cybersecurity Domain, Trends, Vertical market industries, etc.);
• Good knowledge of up to date technologies, applications, products/solutions and platform;
• Effective communication and presentation skills at executive level;
• Proven capability to work in a team and collaborate; with independent accountability;
• Strong communication and negotiation skills with good business acumen;
• Able to perform well in a fast pace and high ambiguity environment
